{"author":{"id":"5e53c9bce7eeb69e347743575f6133426338c29498e200aa8bf1bef46209d02a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1701702469,"nonce":"2/UOP00TbuIuHeomNmU7INTA6ug=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5tmoRv","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5657#issuecomment-1838842991"},"message":"In the case of `mothur_make_shared`, it uses [`from_work_dir` on the logfile output](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/f3a311331dc56461e6aebb365bdd9075c5c9f424/tools/mothur/macros.xml#L136) but it also [moves the work dir output to the output path as part of the command](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/f3a311331dc56461e6aebb365bdd9075c5c9f424/tools/mothur/make.shared.xml#L42). It should do one or the other but not both. This passes ok in Galaxy, but it's an error in Pulsar (and Pulsar's stricter behavior here is probably correct).\n\nThere's also an issue with the glob in the `mv` - running the `version_command` generates `mothur.$(date +%s).logfile`, as does the `command`, so the later `mv mothur.*.logfile $logfile` expands to an invalid `mv` command trying to move two files to a single file path, e.g.:\n\n```command\nmv mothur.1701299851.logfile mothur.1701299852.logfile ../outputs/dataset_4a03f3bd-b44e-45bf-a52b-59954b4f21f9.dat\n```\n\nWhich results in:\n\n```\nmv: can't stat '/corral4/main/jobs/054/014/54014120/outputs/dataset_4a03f3bd-b44e-45bf-a52b-59954b4f21f9.dat/mothur.1701299851.logfile': Not a directory\nmv: can't stat '/corral4/main/jobs/054/014/54014120/outputs/dataset_4a03f3bd-b44e-45bf-a52b-59954b4f21f9.dat/mothur.1701299852.logfile': Not a directory\n```","files":null}]}